				\begin{document}$$ Q_{i} ,\,\,\,\forall \,\,i\, = \,0,\;1,\;2,\; \ldots ,\;n - 1 $$\end{document} in a 3-D coordinate system, the line that connects the nodes Q0(x0, y0, z0), Q1(x1, y1, z1), Q2(x2, y2, z2), …, Qn(xn, yn, zn), in a successive manner is the Z-Curve of the nucleotide sequences being examined. These nodes are mathematically represented as [20, 28]:

